[1/118] [Synthetic Bank] English Primary 6 — QS115  Primary 6  (10.7s)
============================================================
STEM: He always helps his friends with their homework, ___ he? remarked Sarah.
  (1) isn't
  (2) doesn't
  (3) wasn't
  (4) hasn't
ANSWER: (2)

ELABORATION (671 chars):
This question tests **question tags**, which must match the verb and tense of the main statement.

The main verb here is "**helps**", which is in the **simple present tense**. Because the statement is positive, the tag must be negative and use the matching helping verb "**doesn't**", making **(2)** correct!

Here is why the other options are incorrect:
**(1)** fails because "**isn't**" requires an "is" verb in the main sentence (like "He is helping").
**(3)** fails because "**wasn't**" is the wrong tense, used for the **past tense** ("He was helping").
**(4)** fails because "**hasn't**" is the wrong tense, used for the **present perfect tense** ("He has helped").

