[2/118] [Synthetic Bank] English Primary 6 — QS116  Primary 6  (14.0s)
============================================================
STEM: It was Mr. Tan, not his colleagues, who finished the report all by ___," I said.
  (1) themselves
  (2) himself
  (3) herself
  (4) ourselves
ANSWER: (2)

ELABORATION (632 chars):
The rule being tested is **reflexive pronouns**, which must agree with the true **subject** of the sentence.

The actual **subject** doing the action is "Mr. Tan", a singular male. Therefore, we use the singular masculine **reflexive pronoun** "himself", making **(2)** correct!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1)** has a mismatched plural **pronoun** that incorrectly points to the distractors "colleagues" instead of the true **subject**.
**(3)** has a mismatched feminine **pronoun**, but "Mr. Tan" is a masculine name.
**(4)** has a mismatched first-person **pronoun**, which does not match our third-person **subject**.

