[4/118] P5 English EOY Rosyth 2025 — Q1  Primary 5  (11.3s)
============================================================
STEM: While John was playing soccer in the field, someone ___ his bag.
  (1) stole
  (2) steals
  (3) has stolen
  (4) had been stealing
ANSWER: 1

ELABORATION (759 chars):
**The rule**: This question tests the **past continuous tense interrupted by simple past**, where a long ongoing past action is interrupted by a short, sudden action.

**Why the answer is correct**: "Was playing" is the long background action. We use the **simple past tense** in option **(1)** "stole" for the short, sudden action that interrupted him.

**Why each wrong option fails**:
**(2)** "steals" is the **simple present tense**, which clashes with a story happening in the past.
**(3)** "has stolen" is the **present perfect tense**, which links to the present and does not fit a finished past event.
**(4)** "had been stealing" is the **past perfect continuous tense**, which describes a long ongoing action rather than a quick, sudden interruption.

