[5/118] P5 English EOY Rosyth 2025 — Q2  Primary 5  (11.8s)
============================================================
STEM: If the weather permits, the children ___ to the beach for a picnic.
  (1) go
  (2) will go
  (3) had gone
  (4) have gone
ANSWER: 2

ELABORATION (675 chars):
This question tests **First Conditional sentences**, which talk about a real possibility in the future.

The 'if' clause ('If the weather permits') is in the **simple present tense**, so the main clause must use the **simple future tense** ('will go'). That is why **(2)** is correct!

Here is why the other options are wrong:
**(1)** fails because 'go' is in the **simple present tense**, which is used for general facts, not a specific future plan.
**(3)** fails because 'had gone' is in the **past perfect tense**, which does not match a present tense 'if' clause.
**(4)** fails because 'have gone' is in the **present perfect tense**, which does not show a future action.

