[6/118] P5 English EOY Rosyth 2025 — Q3  Primary 5  (12.5s)
============================================================
STEM: At the bus stop, Mrs Tan saw the robber ___ an old lady's handbag before running away.
  (1) snatch
  (2) snatches
  (3) snatched
  (4) was snatching
ANSWER: 1

ELABORATION (663 chars):
This question tests the rule for **sensory verbs** (verbs related to our senses, like see, hear, or feel).

When using a **sensory verb** like "saw" followed by an object ("the robber"), you must use a **bare infinitive** (the base verb with no endings) to show a completed action. Therefore, **(1) snatch** is the correct answer!

**(2)** fails because it has a singular "-es" ending, which cannot follow an object in this pattern.
**(3)** fails because it is in the past tense, but the rule requires a **bare infinitive**.
**(4)** fails because it adds the helping verb "was", breaking the rule (we can use an "-ing" word alone here, but never "was snatching").

