============================================================
STEM: Most of the students , except for Judy, ___ going to watch the fireworks this weekend.
  (1) is
  (2) are
  (3) was
  (4) were
ANSWER: 2

ELABORATION (683 chars):
This question tests **subject-verb agreement** when the main subject is separated from the verb by an extra phrase.

The main subject is the **plural noun phrase** "Most of the students", so we ignore the extra words ", except for Judy,". Since "this weekend" shows a future plan, we need the **plural present tense verb** "are", making **(2)** correct.

Why the other options fail:
**(1)** fails because "is" is a **singular verb**, causing a mismatched subject.
**(3)** fails because "was" is a **singular past tense verb**, so it has the wrong tense and mismatched subject.
**(4)** fails because "were" is a **plural past tense verb**, which is the wrong tense for a future event.

