STEM: "I think either Sue or her group members ___ the first-aid kits," the class monitor told his teacher.
  (1) take
  (2) takes
  (3) has taken
  (4) have taken
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (722 chars):
This question tests **subject-verb agreement** with **either... or**, as well as the **present perfect tense**.

When using **either... or**, the verb must agree with the subject closest to it. The closest subject is the plural "her group members," so we need a **plural verb**. We also need the **present perfect tense** because the action of taking the kits happened recently and is important right now. That is why **(4)** is correct!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1)** uses the **simple present tense**, which describes a habit rather than a completed action.
**(2)** is incorrect because it is a **singular verb** and the wrong **tense**.
**(3)** uses a **singular verb**, but our closest subject is plural.

