  (1) who
  (2) which
  (3) whom
  (4) whose
ANSWER: 3

ELABORATION (566 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **relative pronouns**.

The correct answer is **(3)** because "the man" is the **object** of the action. The police (the subject) commended the man (the object), so we must use the **object pronoun** "**whom**".

Here is why the other options are wrong:
**(1)** fails because "**who**" is a **subject pronoun**, used when the person is doing the action.
**(2)** fails because "**which**" is used for **animals or things**, not people.
**(4)** fails because "**whose**" shows **possession or ownership**, which does not fit here.

