  (1) few
  (2) little
  (3) many
  (4) much
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (534 chars):
This question tests the use of **quantifiers with countable and uncountable nouns**.

The word "**improvement**" here is an **uncountable noun**. Since the coach's pep talk helped the team get a lot better, we use "**much**" to show a large amount of progress!

**(1)** fails because "**few**" is only used for plural **countable nouns**.
**(2)** fails because "**little**" means almost no progress, which contradicts the positive effect of a pep talk.
**(3)** fails because "**many**" is strictly used for plural **countable nouns**.

