============================================================
STEM: Dave and Tom can get along very well with each other ___ they have many differences in their interests.
  (1) so
  (2) since
  (3) though
  (4) because
ANSWER: 3

ELABORATION (729 chars):
**The rule:** This question tests your understanding of **conjunctions of contrast**, which are used to connect two opposing ideas in a sentence.

**Why the answer is correct:** Getting along well is unexpected when two people have very different interests, so the contrasting word **"though"** perfectly connects these opposing facts.

**Why each wrong option fails:**
**(1)** fails because **"so"** is a **conjunction of result**, but having differences is not a result of getting along.
**(2)** fails because **"since"** is a **conjunction of reason**, but having differences is not the reason they get along.
**(4)** fails because **"because"** is also a **conjunction of reason**, which does not fit these contrasting ideas.

